https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-git-on-ubuntu-18-04-quickstart

Step 1:
sudo apt update


Step 2:
sudo apt install git

Step 3:
git --version

Step 4 â€” Set Up Git
Now that you have Git installed and to prevent warnings, you should configure it with your information.

git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "youremail@domain.com"

If you need to edit this file, you can use a text editor such as nano:
nano ~/.gitconfig



~/.gitconfig contents
[user]
  name = Your Name
  email = youremail@domain.com

